  "answer": "**1. In-Depth User Understanding:** Anticipating the believer's need for a foundational truth, the scriptures establish the declaration of faith by revealing that there is no deity except God, instructing humanity to worship Him alone [1]. \n\n**2. Robust and Enduring Framework:** To build a steadfast and resilient structure for the faithful, Surah Al-Baqarah 2:43 mandates the enduring obligations of establishing prayer and giving zakah [2]. \n\n**3. Elegant and Lucid Presentation:** The Quran elegantly presents the command for fasting in Surah Al-Baqarah 2:183, explaining clearly that it is decreed upon believers, just as it was on previous nations, to help them achieve righteousness [3]. \n\n**4. Seamless and Accessible Experience:** To ensure the spiritual journey is accessible, Surah Ali 'Imran 3:97 straightforwardly establishes the pilgrimage to the House as a duty to God, but seamlessly limits this obligation only to those who are physically and financially able to find a way there [4].",
